Free gym passes or £10/mth membership
Are you paying £270 a swim? Don't be a gym turkey - use these
tips to shed the pounds, rather than waste them ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/deals/cheap-gym-membership )
Every January gyms fill up with what the pros call
'turkeys', new joiners who won't last too long after Christmas.
Good intentions can be expensive - far too many lock themselves
into costly unbreakable contracts, like this tweeter: "Paid £270
for a year's membership, went for one swim. Most expensive swim
ever." Full help in Free & Cheap Gyms ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/deals/cheap-gym-membership ) -
here's a warm-up...

* ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/deals/cheap-gym-membership )Free
gym passes. First, check if the gym fits. We've blagged 7-day
British Military Fitness ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/deals/cheap-gym-membership#bmf )
passes, 3-day LA Fitness ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/deals/cheap-gym-membership#LA )
passes and more. See the full Free Gym Pass ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/deals/cheap-gym-membership#bmf )
list.
* Use PAYG gyms - incl FREE £5 credit. No need for a contract,
the site Pay-As-U-Gym ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/deals/cheap-gym-membership#paygym ) allows you to buy one-off passes for lots of different gyms,
plus click the link and we've blagged you £5 credit. Full info on
this & more in One-time Gym Passes ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/deals/cheap-gym-membership#payg ).
* No-frills £10-£20/mth gyms with no contract. If you can live
without a pool (though you don't even need to sacrifice that
sometimes) and sauna, see our full list of exercise-only
No-Frills Gyms ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/deals/cheap-gym-membership#nofrills ).
* Going for a year-long contract? HAGGLE, HAGGLE, HAGGLE. If
you're a gym regular, whether renewing your contract or joining a
new place, January is when many premium gyms have big deals on.
Don't accept standard or even 'promo' prices, negotiate hard (but
politely) to get a hot deal. 'Membership execs' may be paid on
commission and have room to negotiate. Yet be careful, see our
Gym Contract Rights ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/deals/cheap-gym-membership#contracts ) help.
* Do you really need a gym? DIY workouts. Running shoes and
dumbbells (used carefully) can offer a great workout. Try our
MegaShopBot ( http://www.megashopbot.com ) tool or Amazon
Discount Finder ( http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/shopping/cheap-amazon-loopholes#tool_anchor ), which finds running gear at 75
*****************************************************************

For lots more tips, freebies, forum tips, vouchers and MoneySaving, go to http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/latesttip/  

