                       <td class="numbers" valign="top" style="font-size: 15px; color: #777777; vertical-align: top; font-family: Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, serif; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; background-color: #ffffff;" align="center" bgcolor="#ffffff">9.</td>
                       <td style="background-color: #ffffff; font-size: 13px; color: #222;" bgcolor="#ffffff"><strong>...become a haggler every time I renew a contract. </strong> Whether car insurance, broadband, home phone or roadside  recovery, if you auto-renew you&rsquo;re likely paying too much. Companies often just  raise prices each year hoping you&rsquo;ll be apathetic and do nothing.&nbsp;You've two choices:<br />
                           <br />
                             <em>1) Switch.</em> The best deals are usually reserved for new customers as firms push their marketing budgets into promos. For those see our <a href="http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/phones/cheap-broadband?utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=hiya&amp;utm_term=02-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=phones&amp;utm_content=28" style="color: #0047d9;">broadband</a>, <a href="http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/car-insurance/?utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=hiya&amp;utm_term=02-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=car-insurance&amp;utm_content=29" style="color: #0047d9;">car insurance</a>, <a href="http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/phones/home-phone-calls?utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=hiya&amp;utm_term=02-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=phones&amp;utm_content=30" style="color: #0047d9;">home phone</a>, <a href="http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/shopping/cheaper-sky-cheap-cable?utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=hiya&amp;utm_term=02-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=shopping&amp;utm_content=31" style="color: #0047d9;">digital TV</a> and <a href="http://www.moneysavingexpert.com/car-insurance/breakdown-cover?utm_source=MSE_Newsletter&amp;utm_medium=hiya&amp;utm_term=02-Jan-15-v1&amp;utm_campaign=car-insurance&amp;utm_content=32" style="color: #0047d9;">cheap breakdown cover</a> guides.<br /><br />
							 <em>2) Stick but haggle</em>. If you're happy with the service, haggle. The  powerhouse trick is to threaten to leave so you get put through to disconnections,  known internally as &lsquo;customer retentions&rsquo;, as their job's to keep you. In our poll  last month, 86                         Forumite Ma3140 says: <em>&quot;Called Sky and said I was looking at leaving  and taking my TV, broadband and phone to BT or TalkTalk. I was offered a saving of &pound;23.55 per month for a year - a total saving of &pound;283.&quot;</em>
</td>

